DVswitch: a basic video mixer for live DV streams
=================================================

Installation
------------

From version 0.9, DVswitch will use the RTSP and RTP protocols with
the aid of the liveMedia library (aka LIVE555).  It currently requires
a modified version of the library, which is being developed in the git
repository at:
    git://git.debian.org/git/dvswitch/live-dv.git
also available as:
    https://alioth.debian.org/anonscm/git/dvswitch/live-dv.git

You will need to build that first:
    cd ..
    git clone git://git.debian.org/git/dvswitch/live-dv.git
    cd live-dv
    ./genMakefiles linux
    make

Now build DVswitch:
    cd ../dvswitch
    mkdir -p build
    cd build
    cmake -D LiveMedia_BUILDDIR=$PWD/../../live-dv ..
    make

The DVswitch commands will be built in the subdirectory 'build/src'.
You can install them with:
    make install

liveMedia only builds static libraries and does not need to be
installed.
